SonarQube
Scans Java source code for code quality issues — bugs, code smells, duplication, and test coverage. Focuses more on maintainability than security.

Snyk SCA -  Software Composition Analysis
Scans pom.xml and the full transitive dependency tree for known CVEs in open source libraries. Catches third-party risk — vulnerable versions of libs you're using.

Snyk SAST - Static Application Security Testing
Scans your Java source code for security vulnerabilities like SQL injection, hardcoded secrets, and insecure deserialization. Catches first-party risk — bugs in code you wrote.

Sysdig
Scans the built OCI container image sitting in ECR for vulnerabilities. Catches issues that only appear at the image/runtime level — OS packages, base image CVEs — not visible in source code.

pipeline {
    agent any
    stages {
        stage('Checkout') {
            steps {
                git 'https://github.com/example/app.git'
            }
        }
        stage('Build') {
            steps {
                sh 'mvn clean package'
            }
        }
        stage('Run Scans') {
            parallel {
                stage('SonarQube Scan') {
                    steps {
                        sonarQubeScan()
                    }
                }
                stage('Snyk Scan') {
                    steps {
                        // SCA — scan pom.xml + dependency tree
                        sh 'snyk test --all-projects'
                        // SAST — scan Java source code
                        sh 'snyk code test'
                    }
                    post {
                        always {
                            // Publish HTML SCA/SAST report
                            publishHTML(target: [
                                reportName: 'Snyk Report',
                                reportDir: 'snyk-reports',
                                reportFiles: 'index.html'
                            ])
                        }
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        stage('Docker Build') {
            steps {
                sh 'docker build -t myapp:${BUILD_NUMBER} .'
            }
        }
        stage('Push Image') {
            steps {
                sh 'docker push myapp:${BUILD_NUMBER}'
            }
        }
        stage('Sysdig Image Scan') {
            steps {
                // Scans OCI image in ECR for vulnerabilities
                sysdigImageScan imageName: "myapp:${BUILD_NUMBER}"
            }
        }
        stage('Deploy to K8s') {
            steps {
                sh 'kubectl apply -f deployment.yaml'
            }
        }
    }
}
