Composition = what your application is made of (dependencies/libraries).

What composition means in software:

Your Java Spring Boot app
        ↓
composed of:
├── spring-boot 3.1.0
├── log4j 2.14.0        ← vulnerable ❌
├── jackson 2.13.0
├── postgresql 42.3.0   ← vulnerable ❌
├── guava 31.0
└── commons-io 2.11.0

What Snyk SCA does:

Scans your pom.xml / package.json / requirements.txt
        ↓
Finds all dependencies (composition)
        ↓
Checks against vulnerability database (CVE)
        ↓
Reports:
→ log4j 2.14.0 → CVE-2021-44228 (Log4Shell) ❌
→ postgresql 42.3.0 → CVE-2022-21724 ❌
        ↓
Suggests fix:
→ upgrade log4j to 2.17.1 ✅
